Flask-Login

What does this technology (library/framework/service) accomplish for you?
Flask-Login provides user session management for Flask. We can use this technology to implement the common tasks of logging in, logging out, and remembering your usersâ€™ sessions.

How does this technology accomplish what it does?
Installation:  $ pip install flask-login
login_manager = LoginManager()
Above code uses LoginManager class which helps us to load a user from an ID or find where to send users when they need to log in.

@login_manager.user_loader
def load_user(user_id):
return User.get(user_id)
Above code provides a user_loader callback. It is used to reload the user object from the user ID stored in the session.

We also have the user class for represent users. 

Code used: https://flask-login.readthedocs.io/en/latest/

